4:
Ugh, can't believe we have to do
overtime on Halloween...
9:
I know but, aaaghh... If only Mother
Love was here, dressed up to boost
morale...
11:
Eep! I was just k-kidding, of course!
Work is so much fun, haha!
15:
Long time no see, you two. Hard at
work even on Halloween?
19:
Mother Love, I didn't expect to see
you today!
26:
...That was a joke, wasn't it? You
know that isn't the case. Now how
can I be of service?
39:
I'll even accept SoyMate, if you have
any sweet flavors around. Like
chocolate chip cookie.
42:
Don't have any? Hehe, I suppose
you've been too busy working to
think of food.
44: In that case, it's a trick for you.
54:
I've been able to visit so many
different worlds because you let me
go free.
57:
I've seen and learned much. Can
you believe there are worlds where
ghosts actually exist?
60:
...If you witnessed any yourself, I'll
pay for the memory data. I can turn
it into VR horror content.
64:
I have taken everything you gave
me and kept it close to my heart.
66:
Though I still need to learn how to
put the knowledge to good use.
70:
You will certainly get there one day,
Love.
75:
Souvenirs. Some of them will expire,
so eat them soon.
77:
Next time, I hope you'll have some
treats prepared.
81:
Good grief. She's grown quite
rambunctious...
84: I wish Mother Love hugged me too...
89:
...My search today also ends in
failure.
98: Yes, that is me. It has been a while.
102: How... No, never mind. You seem well.
104:
...There's something I've been
meaning to talk to you about
107:
Your mental state seems to be
deteriorating. Do you require
counseling?
114:
I'm just happy you haven't
changed... and that we're able to
speak with one another...
118:
Truly, I'm glad to see you're alive and
well, and I...
120:
I'm so sorry I left you alone... I don't
know how I can ever make up for
abandoning you...
122:
...My apologies, Mother Love. It
seems I am the cause of your
deteriorating mental state.
125:
*sniffle* It's all right. I really am
happy to see you again.
129:
Tell me how you've been doing,
Radius.
131:
Were you able to find freedom for
yourself?
133:
Or... did I force you to do something
you didn't want?
136:
I am sorry, Mother Love, but what is
freedom?
142:
After we parted, I met with
synthetics who acted human and
asked for their data on the meaning
of freedom.
143:
However, they were also unable to
fully comprehend the definition of
the word.
145:
Mother Love, does the free will of an
individual human being affect the
rest of the population?
148:
...Sometimes it does, like when I
forced you to leave.
151:
But I believe that in most cases... it
does not.
153:
If we consider the potential that
individual free will has to affect the
population, then should it be
permissible?
156:
...I'm not sure I understand. What are
you trying to ask?
159:
I am attempting to learn what value
there is in human freedom for
synthetics.
163:
Wait, please... I need a moment to
collect my thoughts.
166:
Are you saying that it's better for you
not to have freedom?
168:
Based on my current findings,
human freedom indicates a
tendency to separate from the
majority.
170:
Such individuality does not
contribute to our potential as it does
for humans.
174:
I see. Or rather... I don't really see at
all.
178:
At the very least, it appears I forced
my ideals of freedom onto you. I'm
sorry for that.
180:
I only wished for you to find
something for yourself out there...
183:
Your mental state seems to have
recovered. Was my answer
sufficient, Mother Love?
190:
Radius, would you tell me more of
what you've been up to?
196:
I can't believe this! While the rest of
the world gets to enjoy Halloween, I
have to work, work, work!
198:
I bet my partner's living it up in
Starview like usual... *sigh* I could
use some attention too, y'know...
207:
Bulleta, I've seen so much since I first
left.
209:
I've met many people. I've been
saved by many people.
212:
Now I've finally saved someone
myself.
214:
...I realize I've barely taken a step
outside our world. Your back still
feels out of reach.
216:
I also don't quite fully understand
Radius either.
218:
But I've done my best, and I'll keep
pushing forward.
220:
So won't you reward me with a
special treat for now?
